{"parentUuid":"b0566b46-3fee-4f57-8dd3-9e17f4f732c3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa041f3ac0f60e829","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ls4sBdHlUWnbKGVGEunvywS7","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (72.5KB). Full output saved to: /config/.claude/projects/-config-workspace-IronClaude/caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5/tool-results/call_ls4sBdHlUWnbKGVGEunvywS7.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\n     1→# Anti-Instincts Gate -- Unified Specification\n     2→\n     3→<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n     4→\n     5→> **Status**: Design Spec -- Ready for Implementation\n     6→> **Created**: 2026-03-17\n     7→> **Protocol**: sc:adversarial Step 5 (Merge Execution)\n     8→> **Co-bases**: V2 (7.60) + V5 (7.55)\n     9→> **Cherry-picks**: V4-2 (Fingerprints), V1-C (Spec Structural Audit), V1-D+V5-2 (Prompt Constraint)\n    10→> **Target module**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/`\n    11→> **Pipeline latency added**: <1s (all checks are pure Python)\n    12→> **LLM calls added**: 0\n    13→\n    14→---\n    15→\n    16→## 1. Problem Statement\n    17→\n    18→<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n    19→\n    20→LLMs exhibit several correlated tendencies when generating multi-phase roadmaps from specifications. These tendencies cause systematic omission of integration wiring, undischarged scaffolding obligations, and dropped code-level requirements -- even when the output passes all existing format and fidelity gates.\n    21→\n    22→The Anti-Instincts Gate is a unified deterministic defense layer that addresses four failure modes simultaneously:\n    23→\n    24→| Failure Mode | Detection Module | Source |\n    25→|---|---|---|\n    26→| Undischarged scaffolding (mocks/stubs never replaced) | `obligation_scanner.py` | V2-A |\n    27→| Missing integration wiring (dispatch tables, registries never populated) | `integration_contracts.py` | V5-1 |\n    28→| Code-level identifier omissions (function names, constants dropped) | `fingerprint.py` | V4-2 |\n    29→| Extraction-stage requirement loss (upstream guard) | `spec_structural_audit.py` | V1-C |\n    30→\n    31→Additionally, a prompt-level prevention layer reduces generation-time omissions:\n    32→\n    33→| Prevention Layer | Target | Source |\n    34→|---|---|---|\n    35→| Integration enumeration block in generate prompt | `prompts.py` | V1-D + V5-2 |\n...\n</persisted-output>"}]},"uuid":"d08f90a2-7993-423f-9011-d737c9dd39b4","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:18.835Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b0566b46-3fee-4f57-8dd3-9e17f4f732c3","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
