{"parentUuid":"0142066f-3ddd-4be3-b42a-b0abaf965f9b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa041f3ac0f60e829","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_WfpmyxH7BQyNo7hdb3sWjbxj","type":"tool_result","content":".dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/base-selection.md:124:| **Prompt constraint for integration enumeration** | V1-D + V5-2 merged | Prevention-layer reduces generation-time omissions | D1 (prevention reduces bug frequency before detection runs) | Modify `build_generate_prompt()` in prompts.py. ~50 lines of prompt text. |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/base-selection.md:130:| **Negative-space prompting** (with V1-E structured output) | V4-3 + V1-E | Adds LLM pipeline step cost; deterministic checks should be proven first | After V2+V5 deterministic checks ship and are validated in shadow mode |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/base-selection.md:206:- `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/prompts.py` (add integration enumeration block)\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:125:[Omitted long matching line]\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:128:[Omitted long matching line]\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:146:[Omitted long matching line]\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:150:| U-012 | V5 | **Integration mechanism taxonomy (7 categories)**: Dict dispatch, plugin registry, callback injection, strategy pattern, middleware chain, event binding, DI container | No other variant enumerates the categories of integration that LLMs typically miss | HIGH coverage: provides a roadmap for expanding pattern libraries. Makes the problem space concrete and bounded. |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:221:3. **V1-D and V5-2** are the same approach (prompt constraint for integration). V5-2's enumeration requirement is stronger; merge.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/diff-analysis.md:236:| P0 | Prompt constraint with integration enumeration | V1-D + V5-2 merged | Prevention | Likely (65%) |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/02-implicit-obligation-tracking.md:159:    for i, (phase_id, phase_content, start_line) in enumerate(sections):\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/02-implicit-obligation-tracking.md:221:    for i, m in enumerate(matches):\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:190:Extend `SemanticCheck` in `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` to support a `context_files` parameter, allowing the check function to receive content from multiple pipeline artifacts. This is architecturally cleaner but requires modifying the shared pipeline model.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:193:# In pipeline/models.py:\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:412:**How it would have caught the cli-portify bug**: The reframed prompt forces the LLM to enumerate spec deliverables and search for each one individually. The spec's `_run_programmatic_step()`, `PROGRAMMATIC_RUNNERS`, and `test_programmatic_step_routing` would each need to be individually located in the roadmap. The LLM would search for them, fail to find them, and report them as uncovered. The adversarial framing (\"your SOLE job is to find gaps\") counteracts completion bias.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:415:- Still LLM-dependent — a sufficiently long spec could cause attention limits to drop items from the enumeration\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:461:- Layer 3 catches it via adversarial enumeration of spec deliverables\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:482:from enum import Enum\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:608:| 3. Negative-Space Prompt | Adversarial enumeration would fail to find dispatch coverage in roadmap | HIGH (reframing counteracts completion bias) |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/04-self-audit-blindness-mitigation.md:625:| `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` | Extend `SemanticCheck` for multi-file access (Option B) | Modify existing (optional) |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/merge-log.md:117:- **Before**: V1-D proposed integration task injection constraint. V5-2 proposed forced integration enumeration block. Both modified `build_generate_prompt()`.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/merge-log.md:120:- **Contradiction resolution**: X-002 (V1-D vs V5-2 overlap). V5-2's enumeration requirement subsumes V1-D's constraint. Merged per refactor-plan Section 1 Change 3.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/merge-log.md:121:- **Validation**: Merged block contains all 4 required elements from refactor-plan: (1) enumerate ALL integration points (V5-2), (2) separate wiring tasks from component implementation (V1-D), (3) `## Integration Wiring Tasks` output section (V5-2), (4) dispatch-table-to-functions anti-pattern named (V1-D).\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:78:| `SprintGatePolicy` | Policy class at `sprint/executor.py:46-89` | Never invoked from sprint loop |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:399:**Concept**: Add a separate LLM pass after roadmap generation that specifically hunts for missing integration tasks, with a structured output format that forces enumeration.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:404:2. Prompt provides the roadmap and asks the LLM to enumerate ALL producer-consumer pairs\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:441:**How it would have caught the cli-portify bug**: The structured enumeration format forces the LLM to explicitly trace each producer to its consumer. When it tries to fill in the \"Wiring Task\" column for `steps/*.py -> PortifyExecutor._execute_step`, it would find no matching task and be forced to write MISSING. The structured table format counteracts the completeness bias because it forces per-pair accountability rather than allowing vague summaries.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:502:3. **E** catches it via structured enumeration even if the ID was dropped (post-generation, LLM with structural constraint)\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:515:- **GateCriteria / SemanticCheck pattern** (`src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py`): All new gates use this existing pattern. No new gate abstractions needed.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/01-completeness-bias-mitigation.md:532:3. **Integration audit prompt effectiveness**: Solution E relies on the LLM faithfully enumerating all producer-consumer pairs. If the same completeness bias makes the LLM skip pairs, the structured table alone may not be sufficient. May need to combine with Solution A's deterministic ID list as a forcing function: \"Here are the 47 FR-NNN IDs. For each one, name the phase that implements it and the phase that integrates it.\"\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/03-local-coherence-trap-mitigation.md:150:Changes to: src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py (extend Step with declared_inputs/outputs)\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/debate-transcript.md:273:**V1 final position**: Structured enumeration (V1-E) produces more auditable output. The per-pair table forces the LLM to name every producer-consumer pair, making gaps visible.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:55:  - Diff analysis X-002 identified the overlap: \"Both propose prompt-level interventions for the generate step... V5-2's enumeration requirement subsumes V1-D's constraint\"\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:56:  - V5-2 demands an explicit integration enumeration section in the roadmap output; V1-D adds the constraint that wiring tasks must be separate from component implementation tasks\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:68:1. Require the LLM to enumerate ALL integration points before generating phases (V5-2)\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:258:#### Change 1: Integration enumeration block in `build_generate_prompt()`\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:267:Before generating the roadmap phases, you MUST first enumerate ALL\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:454:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/prompts.py` | Add integration enumeration block to `build_generate_prompt()`; add 6th comparison dimension to `build_spec_fidelity_prompt()` | V1-D + V5-2 |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:486:7. **prompts.py** -- Add integration enumeration block + 6th fidelity dimension.\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:507:| Negative-space prompting | V4-3 + V1-E output schema | After Phase 1 deterministic checks validated in shadow mode (3+ pipeline runs with zero false positives) | Phase 1 complete |\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/05-pattern-matching-trap-mitigation.md:163:    for i, line in enumerate(lines):\n.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/05-pattern-matching-trap-mitigation.md:220:            for j, 