{"parentUuid":"9f72912f-65fe-44f0-b227-5933a3e900bf","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa041f3ac0f60e829","message":{"id":"resp_0e47c9ca96993a990169b9a22e3360819a9cbef6ba695c407a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":54986,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":1760,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compared `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-quality-agents.md` against the three refactor specs. Key reference files used: `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`.\n\n**ITEM QA-001** — Executor Validation Gate for All Agent Entry Points  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence: QA-001 adds agent-level preflight validation and says invalid input should “emit BLOCKED” in `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-quality-agents.md:25-35`. v3.1 formalizes deterministic gate outcomes and evidence rules in `## 5. Deterministic Gate Decision Contract`, especially `### 5.1 Failure classes` (`policy | transient | system | timeout | unknown`) and `### 5.3 Evidence requirements`, plus the canonical `GateResult.failure_class` in `### 6.1 GateResult` at `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:155-200`. v3.1 also requires explicit `audit_*` states in `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:51-58,98-151`. This aligns with fail-fast blocking on invalid inputs, but v3.1 does not use `BLOCKED` as a canonical gate status or failure class. v3.0 and v3.05 do not materially cover agent entry validation; v3.0’s shadow-mode hook is post-task wiring analysis in `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:537-572`, and v3.05 is roadmap-only in `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:99-101,1398-1399`.  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep the pre-execution validation behavior, but rewrite `emit BLOCKED` to map to the v3.1 audit contract: failed gate / failed audit transition with `failure_class=policy` and required evidence, rather than a standalone `BLOCKED` outcome.\n\n**ITEM QA-002** — Typed State Transitions for Sequential Agent Invocation  \n- Status: CONTRADICTED  \n- Evidence: QA-002 proposes a new `AgentHandoffState` enum in `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` with `TASK_READY`, `EXECUTION_COMPLETE`, `BLOCKED`, `VALIDATED`, and adds emissions in `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/executor.py` `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-quality-agents.md:48-58`. That collides with v3.1’s authoritative audit state model: explicit `audit_*` states are a locked decision (`2.1 Locked decisions`) and the normative state machine is defined in `## 4. Normative State Machine`, with task flow `in_progress -> ready_for_audit_task -> audit_task_running -> audit_task_passed | audit_task_failed` at `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:49-58,98-151`. v3.1 also assigns `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/models.py` as the file for “states/enums/constraints/profile fields” in `### 10.2 File-level change map` `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:336-345`, and defines `GateTransitionEvent` with `from_state` / `to_state` in `### 6.3 Transition event schema` `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:213-225`. That makes sprint/models.py the canonical home and audit_* names the canonical vocabulary. The requested naming-conflict check is affirmative: `TASK_READY/EXECUTION_COMPLETE/BLOCKED/VALIDATED` would create a second, incompatible lifecycle beside `ready_for_audit_task/audit_task_running/audit_task_passed|failed`. v3.0 also modifies `sprint/executor.py` with a post-task shadow-mode hook `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:537-572`, so QA-002’s executor instrumentation would additionally compete for the same integration area, though the primary contradiction is with v3.1’s state model.  \n- Recommendation: REMOVE — as written, this should not ship after v3.1. If the underlying need remains, it must be re-expressed as v3.1-compatible audit transition events in `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/models.py` / transition logging, not as a separate `AgentHandoffState` enum in `pipeline/models.py`.\n\n**ITEM QA-003** — Model Tier Proportionality Policy for Quality Agents  \n- Status: UNAFFECTED  \n- Evidence: QA-003 is a documentation/policy addition for model-tier selection in quality-agent markdown files `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-quality-agents.md:70-81`. None of the three refactors define model-tier policy for `quality-engineer`, `audit-validator`, or `self-review`. v3.1’s “Tier” terminology is gate scope (`Tier-1(task), Tier-2(milestone), Tier-3(release)`) rather than LLM model tier in `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:77-86`, so it is not a direct overlap. v3.0 is about code wiring verification and explicitly preserves existing gate infrastructure `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:913-914`. v3.05 targets roadmap pipeline checks and prompt constraints under `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/` `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:10,99-101,1398-1399`.  \n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS — no refactor spec subsumes or conflicts with this agent model-tier policy.\n\nOverall disposition: `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-quality-agents.md` is only partially preserved after the three refactors. QA-003 remains intact, QA-001 still has value but must be rewritten to use the v3.1 audit-gating contract instead of raw `BLOCKED` semantics, and QA-002 is effectively superseded/invalidated by v3.1’s canonical audit state machine and file ownership for state enums, with an additional integration hotspot overlap in `sprint/executor.py` from v3.0."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"d0eefd83-9cd6-4b42-8ddc-6fe2c7291c61","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:49:51.617Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
